# Configuration Rules
## Always apply

### JSON Configs
- Use consistent indentation (2 spaces)
- Include comments for non-obvious settings
- Validate JSON schema before commits
- Use meaningful key names
- Group related configurations
- Keep consistent structure across similar configs

### YAML Configs
- Use consistent indentation (2 spaces)
- Document all configuration options
- Use anchors and aliases for repeated values
- Keep environment-specific configs separate
- Include default values where appropriate
- Validate YAML syntax

### DeepSpeed Configs
- Document memory requirements
- Specify appropriate optimization level
- Include all necessary parameters
- Validate against DeepSpeed schema
- Document hardware requirements
- Keep staging and production configs separate

### Accelerate Configs
- Document GPU requirements
- Specify appropriate distributed strategy
- Include all necessary parameters
- Keep consistent with project requirements
- Document memory requirements
- Include fallback configurations

### Version Control
- Track configuration changes
- Document breaking changes
- Include example configurations
- Keep backup of working configs
- Version configuration files appropriately
